What happens  next

You must inform all interested parties that it's going to close within 7 days after you submit the request.

Interested parties can include:

members, usually shareholders
creditors
employees


Read the full list of who to tell.

Failure to notify interested parties is an offence. You're advised to obtain and retain some proof of delivery or posting of copies to interested parties.

How to cancel this request

If you need to cancel your request so that  stays on the Register, you can submit a withdrawal to strike off.



